Markers like PTPRZ1, CDH2 (N-cadherin), CRTAC1, MEGF10, NRXN1, L1CAM, and various cell adhesion molecules are characteristic of neural crest-derived cells, including melanocytes, Schwann cells, and potentially some mesenchymal lineages. SPP1 and LPL can also be seen in differentiated mesenchymal cells.), results2(Plasma Cells, B Cells (Activated/Mature),Marker Set 2 is overwhelmingly dominated by immunoglobulin (IG) genes (heavy and light chains, J-chain), which are the hallmark of B cells. The presence of TNFRSF17 (BCMA), MZB1, and specific immunoglobulin isotypes further solidifies this identification. LILRB4 and GPRC5D are also known to be expressed by B cells, particularly plasma cells or certain subsets.), results3(Cytotoxic T Lymphocytes (CTLs - CD8+ T cells), Natural Killer (NK) Cells,Marker Set 3 is characteristic of cytotoxic lymphocytes. The high expression of granzymes, perforin, and cytotoxic T lymphocyte-associated molecules are strong indicators. The presence of CD8A and CD8B points towards CD8+ T cells. Additionally, genes associated with Natural Killer (NK) cells and gamma-delta T cells are also present. IFNG and CCL5 are common cytokines/chemokines produced by activated cytotoxic lymphocytes.)
